  <prompt>Extend `tests/manual/RedisValidationTests.ps1` with: (a) tenant-isolation key-format assertion (keys observed in Redis match `spaarke:tenant:{tenantId}:{resource}:{id}:v{version}` pattern), (b) fail-fast assertion (deployed BFF with bad Redis config errors at startup with expected message). Do NOT rewrite — extend.</prompt>
  <role>Spaarke developer; PowerShell test harness.</role>
  <goal>`RedisValidationTests.ps1` includes new test functions for tenant prefix + fail-fast. Existing tests preserved. Non-zero exit on failure (NFR-02).</goal>
  <context><background>Per spec, existing `RedisValidationTests.ps1` is the post-deploy harness used by `Deploy-RedisCache.ps1 -VerifyOnly`. Extension adds the tenant-isolation invariant + fail-fast assertion.</background><relevant-files><file>tests/manual/RedisValidationTests.ps1</file></relevant-files></context>
  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-02 — fail-fast on key invariants; non-zero exit.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-05 — key format invariant.</constraint>
  </constraints>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-redis-cache-remediation-r1/spec.md</file>
